Text takes a `String` into its initializer, because it only displays it and cannot mutate it. Whatever goes into Text is read-only.
`TextField` takes a Binding&lt;String&gt;, because it mutates the value. The binding connects the TextField and the parent view so it knows about any changes to the input.

e.g.:

    struct ContentView: View {
    
        let title: String = &quot;This is a string&quot;
        @State var inputString: String = &quot;&quot;
    
        var body: some View {
            VStack(alignment: .leading) {
                Text(title)
                TextField(&quot;Here goes a binding&quot;,
                          text: $inputString)
            }
        }
    }

