It is possible to continue to run async code after the response is sent if the async code execution is called before the response is returned.

```
async function someAsyncCode() {
  // Do processing
}

(request, h) =&gt; {
   someAsyncCode()
   return h.response(&#39;hello worl&#39;).code(204).takeover()   
}
```

Since you are not awaiting or returning the promise, the execution of the function &quot;someAsyncCode&quot; will not be blocking the execution flow.

